        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 3:33PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 333 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Grandfalls, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Imperial Reservoir, Grandfalls, and Imperial.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
western and southwestern Texas.</instruction>
